<br>
I attained 185 , mainly, by using my training points. Early in my advancement, I was frustrated with the Spell research quest in South Ro being the only way I knew of to advance Spell Research. I don't really care about pursuing Tradeskills, so I used the points to skill up research. Well, last night I went to the Dark Elf Trainer in Neriak to, once again, shell out a couple hundred plat to Max my research skill, but the Trainer wouldn't increase my skill. She said my skill exceeded her ability to teach. So here I am now trying to find out how to max out my Research skill. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>How do I Max my skill out with out using the Trainer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
~Do I need to just scrounge up tons of lower level spell components and create spells over and over ? <br>
<br>
~Do I need to Find Higher level Spells for my current level and Higher and make those?<br>
<br>
~Are there any quests I can do?<br>
<br>
~ Those of you that Maxed in research, how'd you get there?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance, and If there is another post with this info I seek, I missed it when I looked over these forum posts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quikpick>Quikpick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 665<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/12/03 2:28 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skilling up Research, How did YOU do it?</span><hr size=1> Did they stealth nerf this recently ? I researched the old fashioned way to 176 and then just bought my way to 200. If the trainer will not train you anymore, the easiest way to do it is save those runes used for the level 49 spells. At your level, the places you hunt should drop alot of them. Keep making lots of Ice Comets, etc for skillups. <p><p><P><p align="center"><strong><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55973"><font color="#00CC00">Sage Quikpick Emberlore</a></font><BR><font color="#999999">Sorceress of Chronology</font></strong><BR><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=danoris>Danoris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/12/03 10:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skilling up Research, How did YOU do it?</span><hr size=1> If you plan to get above 185, you'll have to find alot of the newer Ykesha runes to combine or you could hope to have 15 training points at a trainer. Level 49 spells only allow research to hit 185 or 186 max. It's not possible to get over that skill level with old world runes. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=207396" target="top">Master Danoris Magikstorm</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
65 EPIC Arcanist<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=inienofvazaelle>Inien of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 125<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/12/03 11:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skilling up Research, How did YOU do it?</span><hr size=1> Are you sure you were at the head guild trainer?  It's usually the one you turn in your newbie note to.  They can usually train you to 200.  Also, research is level capped, so you can't hit 200 until you're 55. <p>-- <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115281" target="top">Sage Inien Astralwrath</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> Sorceror - Second Rune<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ebonmoon.com/index2.htm" target="top">Shadows of the Ebon Moon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Vazaelle</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 4:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skilling up Research, How did YOU do it?</span><hr size=1> Its lvl based as well so that could be why your not 200 maxed.<br>
<br>
If you plan on buying up runes well lets just say that whatever the trainer asks for is going to seem like spare change.<br>
<br>
F3<br>
<br>
btw about how much did it cost altogether? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xadeus@graffeswizardcompilation>Xadeus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 6:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Visit the PoK wizard trainer</span><hr size=1> The wizard trainer in Plane Of knowledge can train you in Research up to the skill level of 200. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rainblow@graffeswizardcompilation>Rainblow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 10:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: high lvl reserch drops</span><hr size=1> the new Veksar zone drops the 50-60 spell reserch drops fairy often.  in two nights of exploreing for about 3-5hours each i have come up with about 10 different runes.  and of course all the other reserch stuff drops there too.<br>
<br>
as far as skilling up reserch skill goes, i trained mine upat lvl 65. =) <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.sport.rr.com/rainspics/Rainsig3.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dynincallor>Dynincallor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 12:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: high lvl research drops</span><hr size=1> I trained to 200 at the PoK trainer.<br>
<br>
Nearly all of my research skillups were due to training points. I don't use them for anything else.<br>
<br>
At 53, your max research skill should be 190<br>
<br>
I had to wait till 55 to train to 200 <p>Dyn<br>
